  "original_title": "\u0d94\u0dc3\u0dca\u0da7\u0dca\u200d\u0dbb\u0dda\u0dbd\u0dd2\u0dba\u0dcf\u0db1\u0dd4 \u0db8\u0dc4 \u0db6\u0dd0\u0d82\u0d9a\u0dd4\u0dc0 \u0dc3\u0dd2\u0dc0\u0dca\u0dc0\u0dad\u0dcf\u0dc0\u0d9a\u0dca \u0db4\u0ddc\u0dbd\u0dd3 \u0d8b\u0dc3\u0dca\u0dc3\u0dba\u0dd2",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Australia's central bank raises interest rates four times",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Australia's central bank has raised interest rates for a fourth straight month, hinting at more interest rate hikes ahead as it predicts a further slowdown in the economy as well as rapid inflation in the country.",
        "Wrapping up its August policy meeting, the Reserve Bank of Australia (RBA) raised its cash rate by 50 basis points to 1.85%, marking a 175 basis point increase since May, tightening interest rates the hardest since the early 1990s.",
        "In an official press statement, RBA Governor Philip Lowe said inflation was already at its highest level in decades.",
        "He noted that it is expected to reach 7.75% this year and it may take two to three years to return to stable levels.",
        "The Australian central bank, like other central banks around the world, says it faces a difficult balancing act to keep the already sluggish economy from stalling."
      ],
